The paper deals with predicting relationships in dynamic and heterogeneous information networks, which involves machine learning and data mining techniques. The paper also mentions the use of recurrent neural networks and meta-path-based modeling for feature extraction, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.SI and cs.LG. The datasets used in the experiments are related to social networks, movies, and publications, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SOC, cs.IR, and cs.DB. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI and cs.LG, followed by cs.SOC, cs.IR, and cs.DB.
